caption: Table 10: Comparison of the results of different activation functions in Eq.(7).
description: This table presents the results of an ablation study that compares the performance of the proposed KEDGN model using three different activation functions (σ, Sigmoid, Tanh) in Equation 7. The study aims to determine the optimal activation function for modeling the time-varying correlations among variables in irregularly sampled medical time series (ISMTS). The table shows the AUROC and AUPRC scores for each activation function on four different datasets: P19, Physionet, MIMIC-III, and P12. The results indicate that the Tanh activation function performs best across all datasets, achieving the highest AUROC and AUPRC scores.
